# Design: Tenant-Scoped Foreign Keys

## Technical Approach

Enforce tenant ownership at the persistence boundary with atomic SQL `EXISTS` guards inside `CreateContentItem`, `UpdateContentItem`, `CreateTask`, and `UpdateTask`. Guard failures will translate from `pgx.ErrNoRows` into store sentinels, then into typed service validation errors, and finally into HTTP `400` responses with field details.

## Architecture Decisions

| Decision | Options | Choice | Rationale |
|---|---|---|---|
| Integrity enforcement layer | Service pre-flight; SQL guard; both | SQL guard in store | Atomic, race-free, matches `IncrementInviteUse` guarded-write precedent and project standard: persistence invariants live close to SQL. |
| Assignee validation | Global `users` FK only; membership pre-flight; SQL membership guard | SQL guard against `memberships` | `users` is global, so workspace membership is the real tenant boundary. |
| Error contract | Raw strings; store sentinels only; typed service error + handler details | Typed service validation error | Keeps store reusable while giving handlers stable field-level `400` responses. |
| Schema hardening | Composite FKs now; defer migration | Defer composite FKs | Higher migration cost, still does not solve `assignee_id`, and current indexes already make guarded lookups cheap. |

## Data Flow

`POST/PUT content-items or tasks`
â†’ handler decodes JSON
â†’ service validates required fields
â†’ store executes guarded `INSERT/UPDATE`
â†’ guard passes: row returned
â†’ guard fails: `pgx.ErrNoRows`
â†’ store maps to sentinel (`ErrClientNotInWorkspace`, `ErrContentItemNotInWorkspace`, `ErrAssigneeNotInWorkspace`)
â†’ service maps sentinel to `InvalidReferenceError{Field, Message}`
â†’ handler writes `400 { error: { code, message, details.field } }`

Guard shape:

```sql
WITH guard AS (
  SELECT 1
  WHERE ($client_id IS NULL OR EXISTS (...clients...workspace_id = $ws))
    AND ($content_item_id IS NULL OR EXISTS (...content_items...workspace_id = $ws))
    AND ($assignee_id IS NULL OR EXISTS (...memberships...workspace_id = $ws))
)
UPDATE ...
FROM guard
WHERE id = $id AND workspace_id = $ws
RETURNING ...
```

Update methods keep the existing `nil,nil` not-found contract by doing a workspace-scoped existence check only when the guarded update returns no rows and no sentinel matched.

