## Interfaces / Contracts

```go
var (
    ErrClientNotInWorkspace      = errors.New("client not in workspace")
    ErrContentItemNotInWorkspace = errors.New("content item not in workspace")
    ErrAssigneeNotInWorkspace    = errors.New("assignee not in workspace")
)

type InvalidReferenceError struct {
    Field   string `json:"field"`
    Message string `json:"message"`
}
```

Handler response detail shape:

```json
{ "error": { "code": "bad_request", "message": "client_id does not belong to this workspace", "details": { "field": "client_id" } } }
```

## Testing Strategy

| Layer | What to Test | Approach |
|---|---|---|
| Store | Guarded SQL rejects invalid tenant references | Spy DB returns `pgx.ErrNoRows`; assert sentinel mapping and SQL contains `EXISTS` guards. |
| Store | Valid references still write | Triangulation tests return successful rows for same methods. |
| Store | Update not-found remains distinct | Simulate failed guarded update + missing row lookup â†’ `nil, nil`, not sentinel. |
| Service | Sentinel-to-field mapping | Table-driven tests over content/task services with store-generated sentinel errors. |
| HTTP | Error envelope contract | Route tests assert `400`, message, and `details.field` for each invalid reference class. |

